{"label":"spawn","args":{"append_system_prompt":"To delegate self-contained subtasks, emit a <fork> tag with a YAML list of short task labels:\n<fork>\n- Write tests for auth module\n- Update API documentation\n</fork>\nEach task inherits your full conversation context and runs as an independent session. Multiple tasks run concurrently. Use fork when a subtask is self-contained — whether you're parallelizing independent work or delegating a task that benefits from full context inheritance. You'll receive the combined results in a <fork-results> message when all tasks complete.","extra_args":["--model","claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","--disallowed-tools","Task"],"prompt":"Create a file called greeting.txt containing 'Hello from a forked subtask!'. Delegate this as a self-contained fork subtask.","resume":null},"result":{"Ok":null}}
