{"label":"next_event","args":null,"result":{"Ok":{"Claude":{"Claude":{"message":{"content":[{"thinking":"The user wants me to create a file called greeting.txt with the content 'Hello from a forked subtask!' and they want me to delegate this as a self-contained fork subtask.\n\nAccording to the instructions, I can use a <fork> tag to delegate self-contained subtasks. The syntax is:\n```\n<fork>\n- Task description 1\n- Task description 2\n</fork>\n```\n\nSo I should emit a fork tag with a task to create the greeting.txt file. This is a simple, self-contained task that can be executed independently.\n\nLet me do that:","type":"thinking"}],"context_management":null,"id":"msg_018anx6f4EFHyyCAo6SzW4tn","model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","role":"assistant","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"type":"message","usage":{"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":18568,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"cache_creation_input_tokens":18568,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"inference_geo":"not_available","input_tokens":10,"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c83934cf-94e5-4cff-a513-c980fd8ef304","type":"assistant","uuid":"88f0b9a9-a65b-41db-96a6-20ddf811dca5"}}}}}
