{"label":"spawn","args":{"append_system_prompt":"To delegate self-contained subtasks, emit a <fork> tag with a YAML list of short task labels:\n<fork>\n- Write tests for auth module\n- Update API documentation\n</fork>\nEach task inherits your full conversation context and runs as an independent session. Multiple tasks run concurrently. Use fork when a subtask is self-contained — whether you're parallelizing independent work or delegating a task that benefits from full context inheritance. You'll receive the combined results in a <fork-results> message when all tasks complete.","extra_args":["--model","claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","--disallowed-tools","Task"],"prompt":"<fork-results>\n<task label=\"Create greeting.txt with content 'Hello from a forked subtask!'\">\nDone! I've created `greeting.txt` with the content 'Hello from a forked subtask!'.\n</task>\n</fork-results>","resume":"c83934cf-94e5-4cff-a513-c980fd8ef304"},"result":{"Ok":null}}
